-- MTN, Expresso Fined for Breaches in Ghana, Business Day Says
-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 2012-05-09T07:20:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-09/mtn-expresso-fined-for-breaches-in-ghana-business-day-says.html
MTN Ghana, a unit of  MTN Group Ltd. (MTN) ,
and Expresso Telecom, Ghana’s fifth-largest mobile-phone
operator, were fined for service contract breaches, Business Day
reported, citing Paarock VanPercy, director-general of the Ghana
National Communications Authority.  The two companies were fined almost $140,000 in total for
failing to develop infrastructure and services in Ghana’s
Ashanti, Eastern and Western Regions, the Johannesburg-based
newspaper cited VanPercy as saying.  MTN Group isn’t aware of the fine, spokesman  Rich Mkhondo 
said by phone from Johannesburg today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
